<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Cyanide Measurement in Water</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --primary: #2F4F4F;
            --primary-light: #3a5f5f;
            --secondary: #778899;
            --accent: #20B2AA;
            --light-bg: #f5f5f5;
            --dark-text: #2d3748;
            --border-color: #e0e0e0;
            --white: #ffffff;
            --warning: #d9534f;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: var(--light-bg);
            color: var(--dark-text);
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 30px auto;
            padding: 30px;
            background: var(--white);
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0px 4px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        h1 {
            color: var(--primary);
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
            font-size: 2.2rem;
            border-bottom: 2px solid var(--warning);
            padding-bottom: 10px;
        }

        p {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
        }

        .info-section {
            margin-top: 30px;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #f9f2f2;
            border-left: 4px solid var(--warning);
            border-radius: 0 5px 5px 0;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
        }

        .info-section p:last-child {
            margin-bottom: 0;
        }

        .btn {
            display: block;
            margin: 25px auto;
            padding: 12px 25px;
            background-color: var(--warning);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 1rem;
            font-weight: bold;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
        }

        .btn:hover {
            background-color: #c9302c;
            transform: translateY(-2px);
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
        }

        /* Back button */
        .back-button-container {
            position: fixed;
            top: 20px;
            left: 20px;
            z-index: 1000;
        }

        .back-button {
            background-color: var(--primary);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px 15px;
            font-size: 16px;
            cursor: pointer;
            border-radius: 5px;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 5px;
        }

        .back-button:hover {
            background-color: var(--primary-light);
            transform: translateX(-3px);
        }

        /* Highlight important terms */
        .highlight {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: var(--warning);
        }

        .feature-list {
            margin: 20px 0;
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        .feature-list li {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .definition-box {
            background-color: #f9f2f2;
            border-left: 4px solid var(--warning);
            padding: 15px;
            margin: 20px 0;
            border-radius: 0 5px 5px 0;
        }

        .definition-title {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: var(--warning);
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        .sensor-image {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 500px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            display: block;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
        }

        .chemical-formula {
            font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
            font-style: italic;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: var(--warning);
        }

        /* Responsive design */
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .container {
                margin: 15px;
                padding: 20px;
            }
            
            h1 {
                font-size: 1.8rem;
            }
            
            .back-button-container {
                position: relative;
                top: auto;
                left: auto;
                margin-bottom: 15px;
            }
            
            .back-button {
                position: relative;
                margin: 0 auto 20px;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Back to Home Button -->
    <div class="back-button-container">
        <button class="back-button" onclick="goBackHome()">&#8592; Back to Parameters</button>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
        <h1>Cyanide in Water Systems</h1>
        
        <div class="definition-box">
            <div class="definition-title">Cyanide (CN⁻)</div>
            <p>A highly toxic chemical compound containing a <span class="chemical-formula">C≡N</span> functional group (carbon triple-bonded to nitrogen). Exists in various forms including hydrogen cyanide (HCN) and metal cyanide complexes.</p>
        </div>

        <p>Due to its extreme toxicity, cyanide monitoring is critical in industrial processes, mining operations, and water quality management to prevent environmental contamination and protect human health.</p>

        <button class="btn" onclick="toggleInfo()">Show Safety & Measurement Details</button>
        
        <div class="info-section" id="moreInfo" style="display: none;">
            <h2>Forms of Cyanide in Water</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><span class="highlight">Free cyanide:</span> HCN and CN⁻ (most toxic forms)</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Weak acid dissociable (WAD) cyanide:</span> Metal-cyanide complexes that release HCN at pH 4.5</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Total cyanide:</span> All cyanide-containing compounds after strong acid digestion</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Thiocyanate (SCN⁻):</span> Oxidation product of cyanide in wastewater treatment</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Sources and Industrial Uses</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><span class="highlight">Mining:</span> Gold and silver extraction (cyanide leaching)</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Industrial processes:</span> Electroplating, metal cleaning, chemical synthesis</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Natural sources:</span> Certain plants, bacteria, and fungi</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Combustion byproducts:</span> Vehicle exhaust, tobacco smoke</li>
            </ul>

            <img src="images/cyanide-mining.jpg" alt="Cyanide use in gold mining" class="sensor-image">

            <h2>Toxicity and Safety</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><span class="highlight">Lethal dose:</span> As little as 50-200 mg of HCN for an adult</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Exposure routes:</span> Inhalation, ingestion, skin absorption</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Effects:</span> Inhibits cellular respiration by binding to cytochrome oxidase</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Regulatory limits:</span>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Drinking water: 0.2 mg/L (EPA)</li>
                        <li>Aquatic life: 5.2 μg/L chronic exposure (EPA)</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Measurement Techniques</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><span class="highlight">Colorimetric methods:</span> EPA 335.4 (pyridine-barbituric acid)</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Ion-selective electrodes:</span> For free cyanide measurement</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Flow injection analysis (FIA):</span> Automated colorimetric detection</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Distillation methods:</span> For total cyanide determination</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">On-site test kits:</span> For rapid screening</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Treatment and Mitigation</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><span class="highlight">Chemical oxidation:</span> Chlorine, hydrogen peroxide, ozone</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Natural degradation:</span> Photolysis and biodegradation</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Precipitation:</span> With iron salts to form ferrocyanide</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Emergency response:</span> Cyanide antidote kits (amyl nitrite, sodium nitrite, sodium thiosulfate)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        function goBackHome() {
            window.location.href = 'parameters';
        }

        function toggleInfo() {
            const info = document.getElementById("moreInfo");
            const button = document.querySelector(".btn");
            
            if (info.style.display === "none") {
                info.style.display = "block";
                button.textContent = "Hide Safety & Measurement Details";
            } else {
                info.style.display = "none";
                button.textContent = "Show Safety & Measurement Details";
            }
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>